latestPosts.caption:
CALL TO ACTION 💘 Angelito Collective and The Celebration of Black Trans Women Cookout (CBTWC) are proud to come together in a collaboration that honors the power, resilience, and joy of Black trans women. Our shared purpose is to create spaces where our community is seen, celebrated, and supported—where we are not defined by struggle but by the abundance, creativity, and love we cultivate for ourselves and each other.

As we embark on this next chapter, we are looking to raise $50,000 to support this mission. These funds will allow us to continue creating life-affirming spaces, provide direct support to our community members, and build the infrastructure necessary to sustain this work long-term. 

Funds raised will go to support the following:
* Food
* Materials and Equipment 
* Production of BLACK TRANS LOVE Merchandise
* Talent and Entertainment 
* Transportation 
* Sustaining Future Programming

At the heart of our work is the belief that Black trans joy is radical, necessary, and transformative. By merging our efforts, Angelito Collective and CBTWC will create new models of community care and resource-sharing that uplift our people in deeply meaningful ways

We move with passion, care, and deep intentionality, knowing that the love we pour into our community will always return tenfold. Our joy is resistance. Our care is revolutionary. And together, we will continue to redefine what it means to hold space for each other in a world that too often seeks to erase us.

In Love & Solidarity,
The Angelito Collective & The Celebration of Black Trans Women Cookout

Calling all women in Ballroom - both trans and cis! 

This isn’t just a moment — it’s a movement.
Next week, House Lives Matter is hosting the first-ever Women in Ballroom Convening — open to the community . 🖤

This space is by us and for us — a gathering to uplift, reflect, and build. Some sessions will be closed to men so we can speak freely, heal deeply, and strategize powerfully.

Whether you’re a leader or a walker, your voice matters.
We need each other in this room.
Let’s move with intention, let’s move with love, and let’s make space that sustains us.

✨ Register now — link in bio.
#WomenInBallroom #HouseLivesMatter

When Octavia said those words, she named a truth that echoes through generations of Black trans women who’ve demanded space, respect, and joy. Since then, we’ve seen ourselves everywhere from fashion to film, music to movement. We are shaping culture and speaking truth.

This legacy was built by our foremothers, and it’s ours to carry forward. On June 19th, we celebrate the power, presence, and future of Black trans women.

Tickets are currently sold out—but we see the demand and are working to figure it out. Stay close for updates.

Email us at fqhonors@gmail.com 

#femqueenhonors  #legacy
